The flagbearer, Joseph Chapman, faced a brutal reality in the [men's singles](/Squash_at_the_2015_Pan_American_Games_%E2%80%93_Men%27s_singles) event. His tournament lasted for a single match in the Round of 32 against Peru's Andrés Duany Escudero. The loss was swift and unambiguous, with scores of 7–11, 7–11, and a final, crushing 2–11. He did not advance. Obviously.

